examples.en: A boy traded his knife for a pup.
Furs were once traded as currency.
He was traded to the Yankees.
They traded quips over a beer.
They traded him to the Broncos.
The stock traded around $20 a share.
Over a million shares were traded today.
He traded his old car in for a new model.
I traded my pen for a pencil and kept writing.
He traded stocks for one tenth their face value.
I traded seats with her halfway through the show.
He collected cards and traded them with the other boys.
They finally traded in their old junker for a nice new car.
Rumor has it that the manager wants to unload him. Maybe he'll be traded to another team.
